            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-29 13:41:10" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the dead body of a person, especially one which is still unburied{N:001}</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>dead body</Gloss>
                <Gloss>corpse</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though in {S:05800301700022} the Greek text reads literally ‘whose dead bodies fell in the wilderness,’ it would normally be a mistake to translate this clause literally, since it might suggest that the people died while they were still standing, and that only the corpses fell. A more natural equivalent is ‘they died in the wilderness’ or ‘they died and their bodies lay in the wilderness.’</Comments>
